<instructionsection id="PACIA" title="PACIA, PACIA1716, PACIASP, PACIAZ, PACIZA -- A64" type="instruction">
  <docvars>
    <docvar key="isa" value="A64" />
  </docvars>
  <heading>PACIA, PACIA1716, PACIASP, PACIAZ, PACIZA</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Pointer Authentication Code for Instruction address, using key A</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>Pointer Authentication Code for Instruction address, using key A. This instruction computes and inserts a pointer authentication code for an instruction address, using a modifier and key A.</para>
      <para>The address is:</para>
      <list type="unordered">
        <listitem><content>In the general-purpose register that is specified by <syntax>&lt;Xd&gt;</syntax> for <instruction>PACIA</instruction> and <instruction>PACIZA</instruction>.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>In X17, for <instruction>PACIA1716</instruction>.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>In X30, for <instruction>PACIASP</instruction> and <instruction>PACIAZ</instruction>.</content></listitem>
      </list>
      <para>The modifier is:</para>
      <list type="unordered">
        <listitem><content>In the general-purpose register or stack pointer that is specified by <syntax>&lt;Xn|SP&gt;</syntax> for <instruction>PACIA</instruction>.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>The value zero, for <instruction>PACIZA</instruction> and <instruction>PACIAZ</instruction>.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>In X16, for <instruction>PACIA1716</instruction>.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>In SP, for <instruction>PACIASP</instruction>.</content></listitem>
      </list>
    </authored>
  </desc>
